{
  "texts": [
    "The exterior product spaces k R d and k R d are equipped with the mass and the comass norms respectively.",
    "We recall that ifv 1,... v k ∈ R d have norm at most one, then the mass norm of v 1 ∧ • • • ∧ v k is at most one.",
    "Analogous statement holds for the comass norm.",
    "We identify d R d = R via the map λ → λdx 1 ∧ • • • ∧ dx d.(2.1)We recall the following fact concerning the size of pairings.Lemma 2.1.",
    "If v * 1,..., v * k ∈ (R d) * and v 1,..., v k ∈ R d, then |⟨v * 1 ∧ • • • ∧ v * k, v 1 ∧ • • • ∧ v k ⟩| ≤ k j=1 ∥v * j ∥∥v j ∥,where the norms on the right hand side are the Euclidean norm of R d and the dual (also Euclidean) norm of (R d) *.For a map f: R n → R m, the symbol Df (x): R n → R m stands for the Frechét differential off at x."
  ]
